#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure 802.1Q VLAN Tagging Using the Command Line"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In Fedora, the <systemitem class=\"resource\">8021q</systemitem> module is "
"loaded by default. If necessary, you can make sure that the module is loaded "
"by issuing the following command as <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]#&nbsp;<command>modprobe --first-time 8021q</command>\n"
"modprobe: ERROR: could not insert '8021q': Module already in kernel"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To display information about the module, issue the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "~]$&nbsp;<command>modinfo 8021q</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See the <filename>modprobe(8)</filename> man page for more command options."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting Up 802.1Q VLAN Tagging Using ifcfg Files"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configure the parent interface in <filename>/etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/"
"ifcfg-eth<replaceable>X</replaceable></filename>, where <replaceable>X</"
"replaceable> is a unique number corresponding to a specific interface, as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "DEVICE=ethX\n"
"TYPE=Ethernet\n"
"BOOTPROTO=none\n"
"ONBOOT=yes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configure the VLAN interface configuration in the <filename class="
"\"directory\">/etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/</filename> directory. The "
"configuration file name should be the parent interface plus a <literal>.</"
"literal> character plus the VLAN ID number. For example, if the VLAN ID is "
"192, and the parent interface is <replaceable>eth0</replaceable>, then the "
"configuration file name should be <filename>ifcfg-eth0.192</filename>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"DEVICE=ethX.192\n"
"BOOTPROTO=none\n"
"ONBOOT=yes\n"
"IPADDR=192.168.1.1\n"
"PREFIX=24\n"
"NETWORK=192.168.1.0\n"
"VLAN=yes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If there is a need to configure a second VLAN, with for example, VLAN ID "
"193, on the same interface, <replaceable>eth0</replaceable>, add a new file "
"with the name <filename>eth0.193</filename> with the VLAN configuration "
"details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Restart the networking service in order for the changes to take effect. As "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> issue the following command:"
""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "~]#&nbsp;<command>systemctl restart network</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure 802.1Q VLAN Tagging Using ip Commands"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create an 802.1Q VLAN interface on Ethernet interface <replaceable>eth0</"
"replaceable>, with name <replaceable>VLAN8</replaceable> and ID <literal>8</"
"literal>, issue a command as <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem> as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]#&nbsp;<command>ip link add link <replaceable>eth0</replaceable> name "
"<replaceable>eth0.8</replaceable> type vlan id 8</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To view the VLAN, issue the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]$&nbsp;<command>ip -d link show <replaceable>eth0.8</replaceable></"
"command>\n"
"4: eth0.8@eth0: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc "
"noqueue state UP mode DEFAULT\n"
"     link/ether 52:54:00:ce:5f:6c brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff promiscuity 0\n"
"     vlan protocol 802.1Q id 8 &lt;REORDER_HDR&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that the <application>ip</application> utility interprets the VLAN ID "
"as a hexadecimal value if it is preceded by <literal>0x</literal> and as an "
"octal value if it has a leading <literal>0</literal>. This means that in "
"order to assign a VLAN ID with a decimal value of <literal>22</literal>, you "
"must not add any leading zeros."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To remove the VLAN, issue a command as <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem> as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]#&nbsp;<command>ip link delete <replaceable>eth0.8</replaceable></command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"VLAN interfaces created using <application>ip</application> commands at the "
"command prompt will be lost if the system is shutdown or restarted. To "
"configure VLAN interfaces to be persistent after a system restart, use "
"<filename>ifcfg</filename> files. See <xref linkend=\"sec-Setting_Up_802."
"1Q_VLAN_Tagging_Using_ifcfg_Files\" />"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure 802.1Q VLAN Tagging Using the Command Line Tool, nmcli"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To view the available interfaces on the system, issue a command as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]$&nbsp;<command>nmcli con show</command>\n"
"NAME         UUID                                  TYPE            DEVICE\n"
"System eth1  9c92fad9-6ecb-3e6c-eb4d-8a47c6f50c04  802-3-ethernet  eth1\n"
"System eth0  5fb06bd0-0bb0-7ffb-45f1-d6edd65f3e03  802-3-ethernet  eth0"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that the NAME field in the output always denotes the connection ID. It "
"is not the interface name even though it might look the same. The ID can be "
"used in <command>nmcli connection</command> commands to identify a "
"connection. Use the DEVICE name with other applications such as <systemitem "
"class=\"daemon\">firewalld</systemitem>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create an 802.1Q VLAN interface on Ethernet interface <replaceable>eth0</"
"replaceable>, with VLAN interface <replaceable>VLAN10</replaceable> and ID "
"<literal>10</literal>, issue a command as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]$&nbsp;<command>nmcli con add type vlan ifname <replaceable>VLAN10</"
"replaceable> dev <replaceable>eth0</replaceable> id 10</command>\n"
"Connection 'vlan-VLAN10' (37750b4a-8ef5-40e6-be9b-4fb21a4b6d17) successfully "
"added."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that as no <option>con-name</option> was given for the VLAN interface, "
"the name was derived from the interface name by prepending the type. "
"Alternatively, specify a name with the <option>con-name</option> option as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]$&nbsp;<command>nmcli con add type vlan con-name <replaceable>VLAN12</"
"replaceable> dev <replaceable>eth0</replaceable> id 12</command>\n"
"Connection 'VLAN12' (b796c16a-9f5f-441c-835c-f594d40e6533) successfully "
"added."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: bridgehead
#, no-c-format
msgid "Assigning Addresses to VLAN Interfaces"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use the same <application>nmcli</application> commands to assign "
"static and dynamic interface addresses as with any other interface."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, a command to create a VLAN interface with a static <systemitem "
"class=\"protocol\">IPv4</systemitem> address and gateway is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]$&nbsp;<command>nmcli con add type vlan con-name <replaceable>VLAN20</"
