"above the device was specified by its interface name, <literal>eth0</"
"literal>, it can also be specified by the connection UUID or MAC address."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create an 802.1Q VLAN connection profile with ingress priority mapping on "
"Ethernet interface <replaceable>eth1</replaceable>, with name "
"<interface>VLAN1</interface> and ID <literal>13</literal>, issue a command "
"as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]$&nbsp;<command>nmcli con add type vlan con-name <replaceable>VLAN1</"
"replaceable> dev <replaceable>eth2</replaceable> id 13 ingress \"2:3,3:5\"</"
"command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To view all the parameters associated with the VLAN created above, issue a "
"command as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]$&nbsp;<command>nmcli connection show <replaceable>vlan-VLAN10</"
"replaceable></command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To change the MTU, issue a command as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]$&nbsp;<command>nmcli connection modify <replaceable>vlan-VLAN10</"
"replaceable> 802.mtu 1496</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The MTU setting determines the maximum size of the network layer packet. The "
"maximum size of the payload the link-layer frame can carry in turn limits "
"the network layer MTU. For standard Ethernet frames this means an MTU of "
"1500 bytes. It should not be necessary to change the MTU when setting up a "
"VLAN as the link-layer header is increased in size by 4 bytes to accommodate "
"the 802.1Q tag."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At time of writing, <literal>connection.interface-name</literal> and "
"<literal>vlan.interface-name</literal> have to be the same (if they are set)."
" They must therefore be changed simultaneously using <application>nmcli</"
